type: software
title: "ContextGuard: Cryptographic Attestation and Zero-Trust Enforcement Against Supply Chain Attacks in Model Context Protocol Deployments"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-03-22"
repository-code: "https://github.com/sunilgentyala/contextguard"
license: MIT
authors:
  - family-names: Gentyala
    given-names: Sunil
    affiliation: "HCLTech (HCL America Inc.), Dallas, TX, USA"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0005-2642-3479"
    email: sunil.gentyala@ieee.org
abstract: >
  ContextGuard is a zero-trust governance middleware framework for Model Context
  Protocol (MCP) deployments. It implements cryptographic server attestation
  (ECDSA P-256), continuous capability binding for rug pull detection, and
  semantic tool-definition scanning for tool poisoning detection. Evaluated
  against a 30-entry hand-crafted corpus of malicious MCP tool definitions,
  the CVL and DIMS prototype achieves 100.0% precision and 96.7% recall at
  1.005 ms mean authorization latency.
